contract.name: FanbetAlgoLottery
contract.desc:
Represents the Fanbet Lottery smart contract.

    This contract manages the lifecycle of a lottery game, including player registration, ticket purchases,
    ticket submissions, prize distribution, and administrative updates. It interacts with external applications
    such as a randomness beacon and a discount app to ensure fairness and flexibility.

    Attributes:
        administrator (Account): The account with administrative privileges.
        executor (Account): The account responsible for executing critical operations.
        managers (Managers): A list of manager accounts.
        beacon_app (Application): The application ID for the randomness beacon.
        discount_app (Application): The application ID for the discount app.
        ticket_price (UInt): The price of a single ticket.
        prize_pool (UInt): The total prize pool for the current round.
        game_round (UInt): The current game round number.
        decimals (UInt): The decimal precision for ticket prices.
        players (BoxMap[Account, UInt64]): A mapping of player accounts to their application IDs.
        winners (Winners): The winners and their match counts.
        percents (Percents): The percentage distribution for prize allocation.
        commitment (Commitment): The commitment details for the current round.
        reveal (Reveal): The reveal details for the current round.
        game_status (String): The current status of the game (e.g., "Open", "Submission", "Payout").
        bootstrapped (bool): Indicates whether the contract has been bootstrapped.
        committed (bool): Indicates whether a commitment has been submitted.
        revealed (bool): Indicates whether the winning ticket has been revealed.
        reveal_duration (UInt): The duration of the reveal phase.
        submission_duration (UInt): The duration of the submission phase.
        payout_duration (UInt): The duration of the payout phase.
